hese writers distinguished between the patriarchal "father of the nation" and their own paternal figures. In doing so, Bilingual Legacies sheds light on the complexity of Spanish conceptions of gender, language, and family and illustrates how notions of masculinity, authorship, and canon are interrelated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aBiography as a literary form. 0aCatalan literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFamilies in literature. 0aFatherhood in literature. 0aFathers in literature. 0aSex role in literature. 0aSpanish literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSpanish literaturezSpainzBarcelonaxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aBarcelona.  aCarlos Barral.  aCatalan writers.  aClara Janés.  aJuan Goytisolo.  aSpain.  aSpanish Transition.  aSpanish literature.  aTerenci Moix.  aautobiography.  abilingualism.  afather figures.  agender.  aself-writing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754502440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487545024423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487545024/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOO